
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dh_autotools-dev_updateconfig` baraye update kardan file-haye config ke az tarigh autotools sakhte shode-and, ghabl az build ya install pakage Debian estefade mishavad. In dastoor be developer-ha komak mikonad ta config file-ha ra be shekli dorost va automatic update konand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--params` --> 📝 Parametrhaye ezafi be dastoor `update-config` pas dade mishavad.
    🔹 `--name=NAME` --> 🏷️ Name file config ra moshakhas mikonad. Agar name moshakhas nashavad, `debian/packagename.config` estefade mishavad.
    🔹 `--no-auto` --> 🚫 Az update automatic config file-ha jelogiri mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dh_autotools-dev_updateconfig --params="--default-yes"

    🔹 Update config file ba default answer "yes"

    $ dh_autotools-dev_updateconfig --name=myprogram.config

    🔹 Update config file ba name "myprogram.config"

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dh_autotools-dev_updateconfig

    🔹 Dar hale pishfarz, dastoor config file `debian/packagename.config` ra update mikonad. In kar be soorate automatic anjam mishavad va developer niaz nadarad dastoor ra be soorate mostaghel ejra konad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dh_autotools-dev_updateconfig` command is used to update configuration files generated by autotools before the build or installation of a Debian package. This tool helps developers automatically and correctly update configuration files.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--params` --> 📝 Passes extra parameters to the `update-config` command.
    🔹 `--name=NAME` --> 🏷️ Specifies the name of the config file. If no name is specified, `debian/packagename.config` is used.
    🔹 `--no-auto` --> 🚫 Prevents the automatic updating of config files.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dh_autotools-dev_updateconfig --params="--default-yes"

    🔹 Updates the config file with a default answer of "yes."

    $ dh_autotools-dev_updateconfig --name=myprogram.config

    🔹 Updates the config file named "myprogram.config".

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dh_autotools-dev_updateconfig

    🔹 By default, this command updates the config file `debian/packagename.config`. This process is typically automated, and developers don't need to run the command manually.
